
Many health professionals still believe that zzso shorten the lifespan of zzso This situation implies that the ethical doctrine of double effect is often invoked to justify their use in extreme zzso The objective of this study is to revise the evidence existing in the recently published literature regarding the effect on patient survival of zzso used to control disease zzso 

A review of the scientific literature regarding the effects of zzso on symptom control and survival does not provide any evidence that there is an association between these two zzso 

The studies revised have not shown that the use of zzso for symptom control in advanced disease stages or in the last days of life has any effect on patient zzso Similarly, survival was not influenced by either the use of higher or lower doses of zzso or by the practice of administering a double dose at zzso 

